# Lesson 2 News Headline

——A good headline is in itself a good piece of news which is concise(简练、简洁), expressive(有表现力) and attractive(有吸引力的).

---

## The function of headlines:

- Attract reader's attention

- Summarize the news content

- Beautify the layout of the newspaper

## Characteristics of headlines

### Abbreviations and initialisms in headlines （缩写）

####  Abbreviations

- BE - Belgium

- BG - Bulgaria

- CZ - Czeck Republic

- DK - Denmark

- DE - Germany

- AT - Austria

- PL - Poland

- FI - Finland

- SE - Sweden

####  Initialisms

- FBI - Federal Bureau of Investigation
- CIA - Central Intelligence Agency
- UK - the United Kingdom
- AC - alternating current
- A&E - accident and emergency
- BA - Bachelor of Arts
- CNN - Cable News Networks
- MSc - Master of Science
- GOP - Grand Old Party
- GDP - Gross Domestic Product
- CPI - Consumer Price Index
- OPEC - Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries

---

### Word omission in headlines（省略）

#### Omission of articles（冠词省略）

- Republicans say Democrats in Senate will regret move.

- The Republicans say the Democrats in the Senate will regret the move.

#### Omission of linking words（连词省略）
- 常是省略and
- To reduce heart attacks, strokes in the obese, control blood pressure.
- To reduce heart attacks and strokes in the obese, control blood pressure.

#### Omission of verbs and auxillary verbs（动词和助词的省略）
- Formula 2 driver Anthoine Hubert killed in Belgium crash.
- Formula 2 driver Anthoine Hubert was killed in Belgium crash.
#### 练习：
- US, Pakistan in dispute over drone attack that killed six.
- US and Pakistan are in dispute over drone attack that killed six civilians.
- US ambassador to leave China, rejoin family in Seattle.
- US ambassador is to leave China, to rejoin his family in Seattle.

---

### The tenses and voices of headlines（时态、语态）

- Simple present tense 代替 Past tense

- 举例：Texas shootings: Random gun attacks leave five dead.

---

### Rhetoric in headlines（修辞）

  - Simile - 比喻
  - Metaphor - 暗喻
  - Metonymy - 借喻借代
  - Palindorme - 回文
  - Personification - 拟人
  - Parody - 仿拟
  - Pun - 双关
  - Alliteration - 头韵
    - Fight or flight?
    - Beauty and the Beast
    - Pride and Prejudice

---

### Wordings（用词特征）

####  Midget word（小词）

- Air - to make known（宣传）
  - TV airs "facts" on arms delivery.

- Axe - to dismiss from a job（解雇）
  - Governor to axe aide?

- Blaze - fire（爆炸）
  - Tanker blast near Manila.

- Curb - to limit, control（限制）
  - Sunday driving curbs planned.

- Ink - to sign（签署）
  - Thaliand, Malaysia ink sea treaty.

- Probe - investigation（调查）
  - Mayor orders fire probe.

- Soar - to rise rapidly（快速上升）
  - Inflation rate soars.

- Vow - to solemn（庄严宣誓）
  - Police chief vows to catch kidnappers.

- Bid - to attempt（努力争取）
  - Bid to open border.

- Clash - battle; dispute（冲突）
  - Mayor clashes with city council.

- Plea - deeply felt request（恳求）
  - Mother's plea.

####  Complicated modifier（堆砌而成的词组）

- Policy-making body（决策机构）

- Blood-cemented friendship（鲜血凝成的友谊）

- Inflaction-proof deposit（保值储蓄）

- Labour-intensive enterprise（劳动密集型企业）

- Fair-trade agreement（互惠贸易协定）

- Hand-to-mouth pay（温饱工资）

- On-the-job training（在职培训）

- Good-to excellent care（无微不至的关怀）

